This component includes:
Key Features:
Three selection modes: single, multiple (checkboxes), and pair (source/target)
Manga-specific metadata: Vertical text support, RTL indicators, OCR quality badges
Smart grouping: Organizes languages by manga relevance and script families
Quick select chips: One-click common languages (JA/KO/ZH for source, major EU languages for target)
Full keyboard navigation: Arrow keys, Enter, Escape, Tab handling
Accessibility: ARIA labels, live regions, focus management
Search: Filter by name, native name, code, or aliases
Dark mode: CSS custom properties with prefers-color-scheme support
Manga-Specific Optimizations:
Highlights Japanese, Korean, Chinese with "Manga" badges
Shows vertical/RTL text direction indicators
Displays OCR quality ratings for source languages
Script type indicators (Latin, Cyrillic, Hanzi, etc.)

Usage Examples:

// Single source language
<language-selector type="source" mode="single" value="ja"></language-selector>

// Multiple target languages
<language-selector type="target" mode="multiple" value='["en", "es"]'></language-selector>

// Programmatic access
const selector = document.querySelector('language-selector');
selector.addEventListener('change', (e) => {
  console.log('Selected:', e.detail.value);
});